Module kivakit.core.resource
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.path

Class FileName

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.resource.path.FileName
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Named, java.lang.Comparable<FileName>
    public class FileName
extends java.lang.Object
implements Named, java.lang.Comparable<FileName>
    A file name, with a base name and an Extension.

    File names can be created with various factory methods, including methods that produce valid filenames for dates and times as well as the general method parse(String).

    • name() - This filename as a string
    • asPath() - This filename as A FilePath
    • base() - This filename without any extension
    • compoundExtension() - The (possibly compound) extension of this filename, like ".tar" or ".tar.gz"
    • extension() - The final extension of this filename, for example the extension of "data.tar.gz" is ".gz"
    • localDateTime() - This file name parsed as a LocalTime object using the KivaKit DATE_TIME format ("yyyy.MM.dd_h.mma").

    Matching

    • fileMatcher() - A matcher that matches resources with exactly this file name
    • matcher() - A matcher for this file name
    • matches(Pattern) - True if this filename matches the given Pattern

    Checks

    • startsWith(String) - True if this filename starts with the given string
    • endsWith(Extension) - True if this filename ends with the given extension
    • endsWith(String) - True if this filename ends with the given string

    Functional

    • normalized() - This filename normalized for any filesystem using FilePath.normalized().
    • prefixedWith(String) - This filename with the given prefix
    • withExtension(Extension) - This filename with the given extension
    • withoutExtension() - This filename without the final extension
    • withoutExtension(Extension) - This filename without the given final extension if it has that extension
    • withoutCompoundExtension() - This filename without all extensions
    • withSuffix(String) - This filename with the given suffix appended
    • toLowerCase() - This filename in lowercase
    • toUpperCase() - This filename in uppercase
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
